        "text": "It needs to be remembered that Robin also worked in ‘design’ mode, notably during the period when he wrote one of his most characteristic and justifiably admired ’story’ pieces: *Danger and opportunity - Crisis and the new social economy*. Around that time he worked at The Design Centre, and co-authored two ‘design toolkit’ collections of ‘methods’: *Social venturing* \\[Murray et al xxx 2009] and *The open book of social innovation* \\[Murray et al xxx 2010]. These are distinctly over towards the left-side of the ‘dance’ schema and have a design-patternish form; but rather in the nature of the discrete, modular ‘unit operations’ of chemical engineering design - somewhat Lego-like - rather than the ‘sung-together’ form of Alexander pattern language? \n"
